HEADWORD: Rostellum
<hw>Ros*tel"lum</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>; <plu><it>pl.</it>
<plw>Rostella</plw> <pr>(#)</pr>.</plu> <ety>[L. See
<er>Rostel</er>.]</ety> <def>A small beaklike process or extension of
some part; a small rostrum; <as>as, the <ex>rostellum</ex> of the stigma
of violets, or of the operculum of many mosses; the <ex>rostellum</ex>
on the head of a tapeworm.</as></def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

